io.reinert.requestor.core

Interface Registration


  • public interface Registration
    Registration objects returned when a request/response processor is registered (e.g. via Requestor.register), used to deregister.
    Author:
    Danilo Reinert

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void cancel()
      Deregisters the processor associated with this registration if it is still attached to the requestor session.

    • Method Detail

      • cancel

        void cancel()
        Deregisters the processor associated with this registration if it is still attached to the requestor session. If the processor is no longer attached to the session, this is a no-op.
